headline: Is Datadog Stock Outperforming the S&P 500?
summary: Datadog has outperformed the S&P 500 over the past year, and analysts are highly optimistic about the stock’s prospects.

headline: 2 Reasons to Watch DDOG and 1 to Stay Cautious
summary: Datadog’s 33.3% return over the past six months has outpaced the S&P 500 by 16.8%, and its stock price has climbed to $138.60 per share. This was partly thanks to its solid quarterly results, and the run-up might have investors contemplating their next move.
